
[1]chastity

   CHASTITY, n.

   1. Purity of the body; freedom from all unlawful commerce of sexes.
   Before marriage, purity from all commerce of sexes; after marriage,
   fidelity to the marriage bed.

   2. Freedom from obscenity, as in language or conversation.

   3. Freedom from bad mixture; purity in words and phrases.

   4. Purity; unadulterated state; as the chastity of the gospel.
